- @h1 = APPLICATION_NAME
- @subtitle = TAGLINE

#masthead

%section#what
  .page-header
    %h2
      What is Feng Shui?
      %small It's not that I'm lazy. It's that I just don't care.
  .row
    .span6.columns
      %h3 History
      %p In the earlier days of Twitter, engineers used almost any library they were familiar with to meet front-end requirements. Bootstrap began as an answer to the challenges that presented and development quickly accelerated during Twitter’s first Hackweek.
      %p With the help and feedback of many engineers at Twitter, Bootstrap has grown significantly to encompass not only basic styles, but more elegant and durable front-end design patterns.
      %p
        Read more on
        %a{:href => "https://dev.twitter.com/blog/bootstrap-twitter"} dev.twitter.com ›
    .span5.columns
      %h3 Browser support
      %p Bootstrap is tested and supported in major modern browsers like Chrome, Safari, Internet Explorer, and Firefox.
      %ul
        %li Latest Safari
        %li Latest Google Chrome
        %li Firefox 4+
        %li Internet Explorer 7+
        %li Opera 11
    .span5.columns
      %h3 What's included
      %p Bootstrap comes complete with compiled CSS, uncompiled, and example templates.
      %ul
        %li All original .less files
        %li Fully compiled and minified CSS
        %li Complete styleguide documentation
        %li Example page template (more to come soon)

